      {
        "id": 13,
        "title": "",
        "type": "text",
        "gridPos": {
          "h": 5,
          "w": 24,
          "x": 0,
          "y": 41
        },
        "options": {
          "mode": "markdown",
          "content": "### Quick reference\n\n| Metric | Safe zone | Watch out | Danger |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| **Fitness (CTL)** | 25-60 (recreational athlete) | < 20 (detraining) | Sudden jumps > 10/week |\n| **Fatigue (ATL)** | Below your CTL | 1.0-1.5\u00d7 your CTL | > 1.5\u00d7 your CTL |\n| **Form (TSB)** | -10 to +15 | -10 to -30 (overreaching) | Below -30 (injury/illness risk) |\n| **Ramp Rate** | +3 to +5 / week | +5 to +7 / week | Above +7 / week |\n| **Daily TSS** | 30-80 (typical session) | 150+ (very hard day) | 250+ (extreme \u2014 race only) |\n\n**The golden rule:** Never increase your training load by more than 10% per week. If Form drops below -30 for more than a few days, take a rest day \u2014 your immune system is compromised and injury risk spikes."
        }
      }
